description: You can use the AWS::Macie::Master resource in a Macie member account to accept an invitation from a Macie master account. The invitation to the member account must be sent prior to using the AWS::Macie::Master resource to accept the master account's invitation. You can invite a member account by using the InviteMembers operation of the Amazon Macie API, or by creating an AWS::Macie::Member resource.

status.description: A enumeration value that specifies the status of the Macie Session. Valid values are: ENABLED | DISABLED

findingPublishingFrequency.description: A enumeration value that specifies how frequently finding updates are published. Valid values include: FIFTEEN_MINUTES | ONE_HOUR | SIX_HOURS. The default value is SIX_HOURS.

macieId.description: Unique identifier of the Macie session

serviceRole.description: ARN of the service linked role for Macie

updatedAt.description: Unique identifier of the Macie session
